Parameter showSpace of contentbylabel macro does not work. The macro seems to ignore the value in parameter showSpace. When we specify parameter showSpace to true, the macro does not show us the space where the page belongs to.

The following is the steps on how to reproduce the problem:
# Create page contains the following:
{noformat}
parameter showSpace equals to true:
{contentbylabel:label=test|showSpace=true}
parameter showSpace equals to false:
{contentbylabel:label=test|showSpace=false}
{noformat}
# Save it. You will see no difference on the results.

I have tried this in 3.0.0_01 of our CAC, the problem is reproducible. However, when I try this bug in 2.10.3, the bug is not reproducible. The previous version works fine. I have attached screenshot when the above example are used in Confluence 2.10.3 and 3.0.0_01.

