The following [custom style|http://confluence.atlassian.com/display/DOC/Styling+Confluence+with+CSS] will not be applied to Confluence pages:

{code}
h2 { font-size: 24pt }
{code}

There could be more attributes that fall into this category, such as _color_. However, this example will work:

{code}
h2 { font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; }
{code}

As a workaround, apply the "!importance" rule to the attribute, for example:

{code}
h2 { font-size: 24pt !important }
{code}

