The tab is horrible. The "details" are in the advanced tab. The most advanced features ("orphans", etc) are at the top, the rarely-used ones are in the middle, and the most practical ones (RSS, Watch, PDF export) are at the bottom, more or less. The main page real estate is used by the description.  Some functions like converting to personal space are only visible in edit mode (wtf!?), and you also only see the default page in edit mode (it should be displayed in view mode at least).  And it is UGLY.

It will be impossible to make it much worse, so let's try to make it nicer. For example by promoting the most important features. we could for example move the main actions to the right and give them larger buttons, and a brief textual description, so they are more obvious. We should probably rename the menu item from "advanced" to something like "space actions", and then have a little "advanced" tab inside the screen. I don't think that "watching a space" or getting a RSS feed should remain hidden away in an "advanced" tab these days anymore. We need to promote them!

