Currently the new User Status updates and Follower functionality is not implemented (from what I can see in the Confluence 3.0 API) with the ability to create custom Listeners for events (e.g. there are no Events such as UserStatusUpdateEvent or UserStatusCreateConnectionEvent).

This feature is available for other content types (such as pages and blogs) which makes it easy to create plugins which do tasks when these events are fired (e.g. PageEditEvent).

If this feature was implemented it would make it very easy to create plugins which integrated with other applications/services which have similar User Status and follower features (e.g. it could integrate with Twitter, Facebook, Google Waves). There are heaps of other plugins which could be written with this functionality.
